WEBVTT

00:08.800 --> 00:14.600
Black Cat presents Peter Pan, by James Matthew

00:14.600 --> 00:19.620
Barry, adapted by Gina D. B. Clemon, copyright

00:19.620 --> 00:36.760
right, Black Cat Publishing. Chapter 1. The Darling

00:36.760 --> 00:49.600
Family. Wendy, John, and Michael

00:49.600 --> 00:51.720
with a lot of rooms and a garden

00:51.720 --> 00:56.760
outside. They live with their parents, Mr. and

00:56.760 --> 00:57.020
Mrs.

00:57.340 --> 01:02.820
Darling. The darlings are a happy family. Mr.

01:02.900 --> 01:05.760
and Mrs. Darling love their children very much.

01:08.180 --> 01:11.340
Wendy is the first child, and she is

01:11.340 --> 01:16.040
pretty. She has got long, blonde hair and

01:16.040 --> 01:16.700
blue eyes.

01:17.760 --> 01:21.060
John is the second child, and he is

01:21.060 --> 01:24.380
tall and thin. He has got brown hair

01:24.380 --> 01:25.860
and brown eyes,

01:26.320 --> 01:31.100
and he wears glasses. Michael is the third

01:31.100 --> 01:34.860
child, and he has got brown hair and

01:34.860 --> 01:35.680
blue eyes.

01:36.820 --> 01:42.760
The three children are very friendly. Wendy, John,

01:42.960 --> 01:45.220
and Michael like playing in the nursery.

01:45.220 --> 01:49.160
It is a big, sunny nursery, and there

01:49.160 --> 01:52.600
are pictures on the walls. There are a

01:52.600 --> 01:53.900
lot of toys in the nursery.

01:56.080 --> 01:59.900
The children have a nanny called Nana. She

01:59.900 --> 02:03.920
is a big Newfoundland dog. She is a

02:03.920 --> 02:04.980
wonderful nanny,

02:04.980 --> 02:09.780
and looks after the children. She loves them,

02:10.080 --> 02:14.700
and they love her. Her kennel is in

02:14.700 --> 02:15.140
the nursery.

02:16.980 --> 02:21.140
One evening, Mr. and Mrs. Darling put on

02:21.140 --> 02:25.400
some very nice clothes. They are going to

02:25.400 --> 02:26.160
a dinner party

02:26.160 --> 02:30.500
with their friends. Mrs. Darling goes to the

02:30.500 --> 02:33.820
nursery. The children are playing happily.

02:35.400 --> 02:38.900
Wendy sees her mother and says, What a

02:38.900 --> 02:43.820
lovely dress. Yes. Says John.

02:44.500 --> 02:50.040
You are wearing a beautiful dress. Thank you.

02:50.440 --> 02:51.500
Says Mrs. Darling.

02:51.500 --> 02:54.420
Your father and I are going to a

02:54.420 --> 02:58.140
dinner party this evening. Then she looks at

02:58.140 --> 02:59.200
Nana and says,

02:59.920 --> 03:03.660
Nana, it is almost half past eight. It

03:03.660 --> 03:05.680
is time to put the children to bed.

03:07.260 --> 03:10.340
Nana looks at Mrs. Darling with her big

03:10.340 --> 03:13.500
brown eyes and barks.

03:13.500 --> 03:18.060
Roof. Roof. She goes to the bathroom and

03:18.060 --> 03:20.440
turns on the hot water for Michael's bath.

03:21.960 --> 03:26.020
But Michael does not like having baths. No.

03:26.860 --> 03:28.080
Says little Michael.

03:29.040 --> 03:31.820
I don't want to have a bath, and

03:31.820 --> 03:35.340
I don't want to go to bed. Nana

03:35.340 --> 03:38.380
is a good nanny, and the children must

03:38.380 --> 03:39.460
listen to her.

03:40.500 --> 03:44.200
Michael has his bath. Then she gives the

03:44.200 --> 03:47.020
children their pajamas, and they are ready for

03:47.020 --> 03:47.540
bed now.

03:49.100 --> 03:52.240
Mrs. Darling comes to the nursery again and

03:52.240 --> 03:52.560
smiles.

03:53.460 --> 03:58.060
Good work, Nana. The children are ready for

03:58.060 --> 04:02.460
bed. Nana looks at Mrs. Darling and barks.

04:03.460 --> 04:06.360
Then she goes and sits near her cannel.

04:07.420 --> 04:10.520
I can hear a noise outside the window.

04:11.120 --> 04:11.640
Says Wendy.

04:12.380 --> 04:16.460
Yes. Says John. I can hear it too.

04:17.700 --> 04:21.400
Mrs. Darling goes to the nursery window and

04:21.400 --> 04:22.460
is very surprised.

04:23.460 --> 04:27.440
She sees a young boy outside the nursery

04:27.440 --> 04:27.940
window.

04:29.160 --> 04:33.080
Nana barks loudly and shuts the window quickly.

04:34.160 --> 04:37.580
The boy's shadow falls on the floor, and

04:37.580 --> 04:39.200
the young boy flies away.

04:41.320 --> 04:44.280
Who's there? asks Mrs. Darling.

04:45.640 --> 04:49.540
She opens the window and looks outside, but

04:49.540 --> 04:50.940
she can't see anything.

04:51.700 --> 04:55.480
How strange. There's no one here.

04:56.260 --> 04:59.920
She turns around and sees the boy's shadow

04:59.920 --> 05:01.240
on the floor.

05:02.120 --> 05:05.040
Wendy, John and Michael see it too.

05:06.800 --> 05:07.920
What's that?

05:09.000 --> 05:11.980
They ask, looking at the shadow on the

05:11.980 --> 05:12.340
floor.

05:13.180 --> 05:15.320
It's the poor boy's shadow.

05:15.980 --> 05:16.980
Says Mrs. Darling.

05:17.900 --> 05:20.800
What can we do with it? asks Wendy.

05:22.060 --> 05:23.780
Let's put it in the drawer.

05:24.380 --> 05:25.320
Says Mrs. Darling.

05:26.540 --> 05:28.040
The children get into bed.

05:29.000 --> 05:31.140
Mr. Darling takes Nana to the garden.

05:32.160 --> 05:34.360
Then he goes to the sitting room and

05:34.360 --> 05:35.600
waits for Mrs. Darling.

05:36.860 --> 05:40.500
Mrs. Darling sings to Wendy, John and Michael

05:40.500 --> 05:42.220
and kisses them.

05:43.340 --> 05:45.760
She is a wonderful mother.

05:47.160 --> 05:49.720
Soon the three children are sleeping.

05:51.580 --> 05:53.980
Mr. and Mrs. Darling go to their bedroom.

05:55.260 --> 05:57.720
They put on their coats and go to

05:57.720 --> 05:58.500
the dinner party.

06:01.780 --> 06:02.380
London.

06:04.020 --> 06:07.000
The story you are reading starts in London

06:07.000 --> 06:09.480
in the early 1900s.

06:10.440 --> 06:13.260
London is a wonderful city and it is

06:13.260 --> 06:15.100
the capital of the United Kingdom.

06:16.320 --> 06:20.300
Today almost eight million people live there.

06:22.160 --> 06:24.580
London is a very green city.

06:25.680 --> 06:27.620
There are more than three hundred parks.

06:28.640 --> 06:32.400
Hyde Park is a very big park with

06:32.400 --> 06:34.420
more than four thousand trees.

06:35.600 --> 06:38.320
You can go biking in the park or

06:38.320 --> 06:40.660
you can ride a boat on the Serpentine

06:40.660 --> 06:40.980
lake.

06:41.780 --> 06:44.980
In the summer there are music concerts in

06:44.980 --> 06:45.320
the park.

06:46.840 --> 06:50.100
In Kensington Gardens there is a statue of

06:50.100 --> 06:52.920
Peter Pan and a lot of visitors go

06:52.920 --> 06:53.580
and see it.

06:54.820 --> 06:57.820
The River Thames runs through the city and

06:57.820 --> 06:59.320
a lot of bridges cross it.

07:00.320 --> 07:02.240
You can take a lovely boat ride on

07:02.240 --> 07:05.040
the River Thames and ride under Tower Bridge.

07:06.120 --> 07:09.060
Big Ben is the name of an enormous

07:09.060 --> 07:11.700
clock on top of a tall tower.

07:12.680 --> 07:14.700
You can see the tower and the clock

07:14.700 --> 07:18.000
next to the houses of Parliament on the

07:18.000 --> 07:18.520
River Thames.

07:20.100 --> 07:22.420
The Tower of London is a very old

07:22.420 --> 07:23.020
tower.

07:23.900 --> 07:27.240
It was built between ten seventy and eleven

07:27.240 --> 07:27.780
hundred.

07:28.620 --> 07:31.180
You can visit the tower and see the

07:31.180 --> 07:32.420
Queen's crown jewels.

07:34.140 --> 07:36.780
There are always a lot of interesting things

07:36.780 --> 07:38.860
to do and see in London.

07:40.000 --> 07:41.600
There are more than two hundred and forty

07:41.600 --> 07:45.020
important museums and many of them are free.

07:46.020 --> 07:49.100
There are also a lot of important theatres.

07:52.260 --> 07:53.000
Chapter Two

07:53.860 --> 07:54.840
Peter's Shadow

07:56.460 --> 08:00.000
Everything is dark and silent in the nursery.

08:01.020 --> 08:05.300
Wendy John and Michael are sleeping and dreaming.

08:06.720 --> 08:09.880
Outside the nursery window there is a small

08:09.880 --> 08:10.980
ball of light.

08:12.400 --> 08:13.960
The nursery window is open.

08:15.060 --> 08:18.760
Suddenly the small ball of light comes into

08:18.760 --> 08:22.620
the nursery through the window and flies around.

08:22.620 --> 08:27.540
It is a fairy called Tinkerbell.

08:28.420 --> 08:31.640
She is very small and lovely.

08:34.540 --> 08:38.800
She is looking for something inside the nursery.

08:40.380 --> 08:44.100
After a moment a young boy comes into

08:44.100 --> 08:46.880
the nursery through the open window and looks

08:46.880 --> 08:47.360
around.

08:48.700 --> 08:52.180
Tink, he says, where are you?

08:53.100 --> 08:56.660
Where is my shadow? Please find it.

08:57.800 --> 09:01.940
Tinkerbell flies around the nursery and stops near

09:01.940 --> 09:02.460
a drawer.

09:03.660 --> 09:07.460
She opens it carefully and finds his shadow.

09:08.280 --> 09:09.600
Then she gives it to him.

09:11.100 --> 09:14.740
Thank you Tink, says the boy happily.

09:14.740 --> 09:18.040
He goes to the bathroom and gets some

09:18.040 --> 09:18.420
soap.

09:19.120 --> 09:21.760
Now I can put the shadow on my

09:21.760 --> 09:23.540
feet with some soap.

09:24.480 --> 09:26.560
He tries to stick it on his feet,

09:27.080 --> 09:28.320
but he can't.

09:29.080 --> 09:32.120
Why can't I put my shadow on my

09:32.120 --> 09:32.600
feet?

09:33.340 --> 09:33.780
He thinks.

09:35.100 --> 09:37.560
Now I haven't got a shadow.

09:38.740 --> 09:42.080
He is very sad and starts to cry.

09:42.080 --> 09:47.140
Wendy hears the boy crying and she wakes

09:47.140 --> 09:47.520
up.

09:48.640 --> 09:51.500
She sees a young boy, but she is

09:51.500 --> 09:52.000
not afraid.

09:53.180 --> 09:55.920
He has got red hair and a friendly

09:55.920 --> 09:56.400
face.

09:57.420 --> 10:01.080
His clothes are made of green leaves. She

10:01.080 --> 10:01.400
thinks.

10:02.320 --> 10:05.320
What's this boy doing in the nursery?

10:06.700 --> 10:09.700
Little boy, why are you crying?

10:09.700 --> 10:14.220
Wendy asks. The boy smiles and asks,

10:14.740 --> 10:16.280
What's your name?

10:17.260 --> 10:21.680
My name's Wendy Moira Angela Darling.

10:22.480 --> 10:23.520
And what's yours?

10:24.500 --> 10:25.240
Peter Pan.

10:25.880 --> 10:26.920
Is that all?

10:27.480 --> 10:29.280
Asks Wendy looking at him.

10:29.900 --> 10:31.540
Yes, that's all.

10:32.060 --> 10:32.700
Says Peter.

10:33.780 --> 10:37.860
Then he thinks, my name is very short.

10:38.860 --> 10:41.640
Wendy looks at his shadow on the floor

10:41.640 --> 10:42.440
and says,

10:43.160 --> 10:44.680
Is this your shadow?

10:45.320 --> 10:45.880
Yes.

10:46.460 --> 10:47.100
Says Peter.

10:47.880 --> 10:49.460
But I can't put it on.

10:50.060 --> 10:51.600
Wendy smiles and says,

10:52.440 --> 10:53.960
I can sew it on.

10:54.820 --> 10:56.120
Can you?

10:56.900 --> 10:58.420
Oh please do it.

10:58.980 --> 11:00.280
Says Peter happily.

11:01.460 --> 11:05.480
Wendy gets her big sewing basket and so's

11:05.480 --> 11:07.060
on Peter's shadow carefully.

11:07.060 --> 11:10.660
Peter looks at her and is very glad.

11:11.640 --> 11:14.200
After a few minutes Wendy says,

11:14.740 --> 11:15.500
I finished.

11:16.660 --> 11:19.160
Now you've got your shadow again.

11:20.140 --> 11:22.860
Peter looks at the floor and he can

11:22.860 --> 11:23.720
see his shadow.

11:24.600 --> 11:27.460
He is happy and he dances around the

11:27.460 --> 11:27.820
nursery.

11:30.020 --> 11:31.500
Thank you Wendy.

11:32.200 --> 11:32.660
He says,

11:33.340 --> 11:35.080
You're a wonderful girl.

11:35.080 --> 11:37.800
Do you really think so?

11:38.180 --> 11:39.000
Asks Wendy.

11:39.640 --> 11:41.000
Yes, I do.

11:41.460 --> 11:43.040
Says Peter, looking at Wendy.

11:44.320 --> 11:47.500
Wendy smiles and gives Peter a kiss on

11:47.500 --> 11:47.860
the cheek.

11:48.740 --> 11:49.020
Oh.

11:49.780 --> 11:50.580
Says Peter.

11:51.420 --> 11:52.240
That's nice.

11:53.300 --> 11:55.540
How old are you Peter?

11:56.180 --> 11:56.880
Asks Wendy.

11:58.040 --> 11:59.960
Peter thinks for a moment and says,

12:00.880 --> 12:01.480
I don't know.

12:01.480 --> 12:04.780
But I'm young and I don't want to

12:04.780 --> 12:05.240
grow up.

12:05.820 --> 12:08.240
I don't want to become an adult.

12:09.080 --> 12:12.400
I want to be a boy forever and

12:12.400 --> 12:13.800
have lots of fun.

12:15.120 --> 12:18.320
Wendy listens to Peter and is surprised.

12:19.240 --> 12:21.520
Then Peter looks for his fairy.

12:22.720 --> 12:25.920
Suddenly he hears a noise and looks in

12:25.920 --> 12:26.200
a drawer.

12:27.320 --> 12:29.100
Little Tinkerbell flies out.

12:29.100 --> 12:31.660
Wendy is happy to see a fairy.

12:32.880 --> 12:33.980
But Tinkerbell is afraid.

12:34.880 --> 12:36.820
She hides behind the big clock.

12:37.780 --> 12:39.400
Where do you live Peter?

12:40.140 --> 12:40.800
Asks Wendy.

12:41.640 --> 12:44.520
I sometimes live in Kensington Gardens.

12:45.620 --> 12:46.280
Says Peter.

12:47.300 --> 12:49.680
But most of the time I live in

12:49.680 --> 12:51.460
Neverland with the Lost Boys.

12:52.520 --> 12:54.640
Wendy does not understand.

12:56.180 --> 12:56.940
Neverland?

12:57.800 --> 12:59.560
The Lost Boys?

13:00.480 --> 13:01.580
Who are they?

13:02.240 --> 13:05.800
The Lost Boys haven't got a mother or

13:05.800 --> 13:06.360
father.

13:06.900 --> 13:07.480
Says Peter.

13:08.260 --> 13:11.080
They're alone in the world and they live

13:11.080 --> 13:11.920
in Neverland.

13:12.580 --> 13:13.900
I'm their captain.

13:14.680 --> 13:15.200
Oh.

13:15.780 --> 13:18.640
Neverland sounds like a wonderful place.

13:19.320 --> 13:20.020
Says Wendy.

13:20.960 --> 13:21.520
It is.

13:22.020 --> 13:22.680
Says Peter.

13:23.320 --> 13:25.380
And we have lots of fun there.

13:25.380 --> 13:28.860
In Neverland, we fight the pirates.

13:29.740 --> 13:33.920
We swim in the lagoon with beautiful mermaids.

13:34.480 --> 13:37.120
A lot of lovely fairies live in the

13:37.120 --> 13:38.400
trees in the forest.

13:39.140 --> 13:40.000
They're my friends.

13:40.640 --> 13:41.520
What fun?

13:42.120 --> 13:42.720
Says Wendy.

13:43.520 --> 13:46.800
Well, I must go back to Neverland now.

13:47.200 --> 13:47.760
Says Peter.

13:48.320 --> 13:50.720
I must tell the Lost Boys a story.

13:51.420 --> 13:53.380
You know, they love stories.

13:54.220 --> 13:56.740
I know a lot of stories.

13:57.320 --> 13:58.000
Says Wendy.

13:59.020 --> 14:01.060
Then come with me to Neverland.

14:01.440 --> 14:02.040
Says Peter.

14:02.840 --> 14:04.860
You can tell us lots of stories.

14:05.680 --> 14:08.620
And you can see the beautiful mermaids in

14:08.620 --> 14:09.200
the lagoon.

14:09.800 --> 14:11.280
Come with me.

14:11.720 --> 14:13.260
We all want a mother.

14:13.920 --> 14:14.280
Oh.

14:14.800 --> 14:16.320
I can't come with you.

14:16.620 --> 14:17.160
Says Wendy.

14:17.740 --> 14:18.640
I can't fly.

14:19.380 --> 14:21.340
I can teach you to fly.

14:21.340 --> 14:22.720
Says Peter.

14:23.240 --> 14:24.520
It's very easy.

14:25.180 --> 14:28.860
Can you teach John and Michael to fly

14:28.860 --> 14:29.340
too?

14:29.780 --> 14:30.400
asks Wendy.

14:31.080 --> 14:31.560
Of course.

14:32.440 --> 14:32.820
Says Peter.

14:33.920 --> 14:37.500
Wendy goes to John and Michael and says...

14:37.500 --> 14:38.020
Wake up.

14:38.680 --> 14:39.240
Quickly.

14:40.580 --> 14:41.500
Peter Pan is here.

14:42.240 --> 14:43.760
He's from Neverland.

14:44.640 --> 14:45.780
It's a fun place.

14:46.560 --> 14:48.620
John and Michael wake up.

14:48.620 --> 14:50.880
And they are very surprised.

14:51.640 --> 14:54.400
We can go to Neverland with him.

14:55.080 --> 14:55.700
Says Wendy.

14:56.400 --> 14:58.280
But we must learn to fly.

14:59.080 --> 15:00.220
That's difficult.

15:01.060 --> 15:01.740
Says John.

15:02.420 --> 15:03.360
No, it's not.

15:03.940 --> 15:04.580
Says Peter.

15:05.520 --> 15:06.060
Look at me.

15:07.040 --> 15:09.380
Peter flies around the nursery.

15:10.260 --> 15:11.460
And the children look at him.

15:12.220 --> 15:14.580
They are excited and try to fly.

15:14.580 --> 15:17.960
But they fall on the beds and on

15:17.960 --> 15:18.460
the floor.

15:19.460 --> 15:20.620
It's impossible.

15:22.320 --> 15:23.760
They say...

15:23.760 --> 15:26.040
You need some fairy dust.

15:27.080 --> 15:28.620
Says Peter laughing.

15:29.700 --> 15:31.960
He puts some fairy dust on their heads.

15:32.940 --> 15:34.220
Now try again.

15:35.620 --> 15:38.100
Wendy, John and Michael can fly now.

15:39.080 --> 15:40.960
And they are very happy.

15:42.860 --> 15:45.540
Look, I can fly.

15:46.500 --> 15:47.140
Says Wendy.

15:47.700 --> 15:49.000
We can too.

15:50.340 --> 15:52.100
Say John and Michael.

15:52.660 --> 15:55.480
Now we can go to Neverland with Peter.

15:56.300 --> 15:57.540
Says Wendy happily.

15:58.780 --> 15:59.520
Tink.

16:00.400 --> 16:00.980
Says Peter.

16:01.960 --> 16:04.020
Show us the way to Neverland.

16:05.400 --> 16:08.820
They follow Tinkerbell and fly out of the

16:08.820 --> 16:09.640
nursery window.

16:10.700 --> 16:12.720
There are a lot of stars in the

16:12.720 --> 16:13.240
night sky.

16:14.640 --> 16:17.160
In the garden, Nana looks at the sky

16:17.160 --> 16:18.460
and barks loudly.

16:20.060 --> 16:20.360
Wooo!

16:22.440 --> 16:25.100
Mr. and Mrs. Darling return from the dinner

16:25.100 --> 16:27.000
party at 11 o'clock.

16:28.160 --> 16:29.080
They go to the nursery.

16:30.580 --> 16:31.380
But it is empty.

16:32.900 --> 16:34.220
Where are the children?

16:37.100 --> 16:38.680
Chapter 3.

16:39.560 --> 16:40.480
Neverland.

16:41.760 --> 16:45.560
Wendy, John and Michael fly over London.

16:46.560 --> 16:49.600
They see the river Thames and Tower Bridge.

16:50.660 --> 16:52.940
There are hundreds of lights in the city.

16:53.980 --> 16:58.240
Then they fly over big cities, small towns,

16:58.920 --> 17:01.660
tall mountains, green forests,

17:01.660 --> 17:03.680
and blue seas.

17:04.660 --> 17:07.780
At last, they see an island in the

17:07.780 --> 17:08.680
sea below them.

17:09.540 --> 17:12.320
It is a beautiful island.

17:13.680 --> 17:15.160
That's Neverland.

17:15.780 --> 17:17.980
Says Peter looking down at the island.

17:18.960 --> 17:20.380
It is a sunny day now.

17:21.160 --> 17:21.700
But it's Wendy.

17:23.340 --> 17:24.160
Neverland.

17:25.420 --> 17:27.400
Say the children happily.

17:28.260 --> 17:29.020
Look, John.

17:29.020 --> 17:30.180
Says Wendy.

17:30.760 --> 17:32.020
There's the lagoon.

17:32.600 --> 17:34.680
And there's the big forest.

17:35.300 --> 17:35.960
Says Michael.

17:37.460 --> 17:39.520
The three children are excited.

17:41.000 --> 17:43.160
The lost boys live in the green forest

17:43.160 --> 17:45.760
in a secret underground home.

17:46.740 --> 17:48.480
There are six lost boys.

17:49.280 --> 17:52.820
And their names are Curly, Nibs,

17:53.500 --> 17:56.460
Tootles, Slightly Soiled and the Twins.

17:57.460 --> 18:00.020
They are waiting for Peter in the underground

18:00.020 --> 18:00.520
home.

18:02.060 --> 18:05.040
Suddenly they hear the voices of the pirates.

18:06.180 --> 18:08.460
I thought I'm certain there were five of

18:08.460 --> 18:08.660
them.

18:08.960 --> 18:10.620
You want your eyes examined in boy?

18:10.900 --> 18:11.480
Pass me that rope.

18:12.120 --> 18:13.940
I can hear the pirates.

18:15.200 --> 18:16.440
Says Tootles.

18:16.940 --> 18:18.260
They're in the forest.

18:19.360 --> 18:21.520
I'm afraid of them.

18:22.320 --> 18:23.880
Says Slightly Soiled.

18:24.660 --> 18:25.900
What can we do?

18:26.720 --> 18:27.600
Asks Curly.

18:28.280 --> 18:29.860
I'm not afraid of the pirates.

18:30.840 --> 18:31.700
Says Nibs.

18:32.600 --> 18:34.700
He goes out of the underground home.

18:35.620 --> 18:38.480
He hides behind a big tree and looks

18:38.480 --> 18:38.900
around.

18:40.020 --> 18:41.820
He sees the terrible pirates.

18:42.800 --> 18:45.640
They are walking in the forest and they

18:45.640 --> 18:47.560
are big and strong.

18:48.440 --> 18:51.840
They live on a pirate ship called the

18:51.840 --> 18:52.480
Jolly Roger.

18:53.720 --> 18:56.640
The pirates captain is James Hook.

18:57.680 --> 19:01.540
He is a very bad pirate.

19:02.680 --> 19:06.920
He has got black eyes, black hair and

19:06.920 --> 19:08.840
a big black beard.

19:10.080 --> 19:11.840
He hates Peter Pan.

19:12.600 --> 19:14.340
He has got only one hand.

19:15.300 --> 19:17.640
The other hand is a hook.

19:18.620 --> 19:21.620
In the past Peter cut off Captain Hook's

19:21.620 --> 19:23.560
right arm during a fight.

19:24.940 --> 19:28.240
A crocodile ate the arm because crocodiles are

19:28.240 --> 19:28.920
always hungry.

19:30.340 --> 19:34.600
Now the crocodile follows Captain Hook everywhere because

19:34.600 --> 19:35.620
he wants to eat him.

19:36.760 --> 19:40.040
The crocodile has an alarm clock in its

19:40.040 --> 19:40.480
stomach.

19:41.480 --> 19:44.680
Captain Hook can always hear it.

19:46.400 --> 19:49.600
We must find Peter Pan and the lost

19:49.600 --> 19:50.220
boys.

19:51.180 --> 19:53.340
Says Captain Hook angrily.

19:54.260 --> 19:58.180
I know they live in this forest, but

19:58.180 --> 19:58.520
where?

20:00.320 --> 20:04.140
The pirates look everywhere, but they cannot find

20:04.140 --> 20:05.840
the secret underground home.

20:06.840 --> 20:11.220
Suddenly Captain Hook hears the alarm clock tick

20:11.220 --> 20:13.960
tock tick tock.

20:15.840 --> 20:19.940
The crocodile is near Christ Captain Hook.

20:20.680 --> 20:21.800
He wants to eat me.

20:22.380 --> 20:24.380
We must leave the forest quickly.

20:26.020 --> 20:29.260
He runs away and the pirates follow him.

20:30.000 --> 20:33.840
Soon some American Indians come to the forest.

20:34.500 --> 20:38.640
They walk silently and carry bows and arrows.

20:39.760 --> 20:41.160
They are looking for the pirates.

20:42.300 --> 20:43.780
The pirates are their enemies.

20:45.100 --> 20:47.240
Their leader is Tiger Lily.

20:48.320 --> 20:51.020
She is the lovely daughter of the American

20:51.020 --> 20:52.100
Indian chief.

20:53.040 --> 20:54.780
She likes Peter Pan a lot.

20:55.800 --> 20:58.800
The Indians cannot find the pirates and they

20:58.800 --> 20:59.680
soon go away.

21:00.540 --> 21:03.320
Now the lost boys can leave the underground

21:03.320 --> 21:05.520
home and play in the forest.

21:06.760 --> 21:08.940
Nibs looks at the sky and says,

21:09.540 --> 21:12.420
Look, there's a white bird in the sky.

21:13.160 --> 21:15.700
The lost boys look at the sky and

21:15.700 --> 21:16.480
Curly asks,

21:17.060 --> 21:18.660
Is it really a bird?

21:19.720 --> 21:21.360
Of course it's a bird.

21:22.220 --> 21:23.200
Says Tinkerbell.

21:23.880 --> 21:27.760
It's a windy bird. You must shoot it.

21:29.380 --> 21:32.260
Sometimes Tinkerbell is a bad fairy.

21:33.360 --> 21:36.000
She knows that it is windy, but she

21:36.000 --> 21:36.940
doesn't like her.

21:37.920 --> 21:40.180
Nibs takes his bow and arrow and looks

21:40.180 --> 21:40.840
at the sky.

21:41.600 --> 21:44.340
He shoots windy and she falls to the

21:44.340 --> 21:44.640
ground.

21:45.840 --> 21:47.980
Then the lost boys go and see windy.

21:49.500 --> 21:51.100
She's not a bird.

21:52.600 --> 21:53.440
They say,

21:53.440 --> 21:56.480
She's a lovely girl.

21:58.260 --> 22:02.040
Peter flies down with John and Michael and

22:02.040 --> 22:02.380
asks,

22:02.920 --> 22:04.300
Where's windy?

22:05.120 --> 22:05.980
Tutels says,

22:06.740 --> 22:08.320
Here she is.

22:08.740 --> 22:10.500
Peter goes to her and asks,

22:11.020 --> 22:13.720
Wendy, are you all right?

22:14.460 --> 22:17.960
Wendy slowly opens her eyes and smiles at

22:17.960 --> 22:18.180
Peter.

22:18.900 --> 22:21.160
Yes, I'm all right.

22:21.160 --> 22:22.140
She says,

22:22.580 --> 22:26.020
I'm lucky because the arrow hit the button

22:26.020 --> 22:27.020
of my night dress.

22:27.940 --> 22:30.600
The lost boys are very sorry.

22:31.300 --> 22:32.520
Poor Wendy.

22:33.520 --> 22:34.340
Says Curly.

22:34.960 --> 22:36.240
What can we do?

22:37.460 --> 22:39.580
I've got a good idea.

22:40.080 --> 22:41.480
Says slightly soiled.

22:42.460 --> 22:45.180
We can build her a little house.

22:46.020 --> 22:48.120
When the little house is ready,

22:48.120 --> 22:50.360
the lost boys go and tell Wendy.

22:51.040 --> 22:54.500
Come and see the little house, Wendy.

22:54.980 --> 22:55.820
Says Tutels.

22:56.920 --> 22:58.660
Do you like it?

22:59.440 --> 23:00.980
Ask the lost boys.

23:01.660 --> 23:03.700
Yes, I do.

23:04.240 --> 23:05.480
Says Wendy happily.

23:06.180 --> 23:07.800
It's a nice little house.

23:08.640 --> 23:09.360
Thank you.

23:10.100 --> 23:10.340
Wendy,

23:11.540 --> 23:13.280
Can you be our mother now?

23:13.280 --> 23:14.860
asks nibs.

23:15.520 --> 23:19.120
Can you tell us bedtime stories before we

23:19.120 --> 23:19.960
go to bed?

23:20.840 --> 23:22.400
Yes, please.

23:23.160 --> 23:24.040
Says Tutels.

23:24.600 --> 23:26.800
Come and be our mother.

23:27.820 --> 23:28.700
Of course.

23:29.460 --> 23:30.080
Says Wendy.

23:31.060 --> 23:33.400
Come in and I can tell you the

23:33.400 --> 23:34.780
story of Cinderella.

23:36.220 --> 23:40.520
They listen to Wendy's story and like it

23:40.520 --> 23:41.340
a lot.

23:45.160 --> 23:47.000
Fairies and their magic.

23:48.120 --> 23:51.720
People all over the world have stories about

23:51.720 --> 23:53.480
fairies and their magic.

23:54.440 --> 23:56.860
Some of these stories are very old and

23:56.860 --> 23:59.260
some of them are called fairy tales.

24:00.380 --> 24:03.960
Fairies are part of the British, Irish, Northern

24:03.960 --> 24:06.460
European and old cultures.

24:07.680 --> 24:11.680
In Peter Pan, Tinkerbell is Peter's fairy.

24:13.100 --> 24:15.840
Peter says that the fairies in Neverland are

24:15.840 --> 24:16.600
his good friends.

24:17.980 --> 24:21.120
In Pinocchio, there is a kind fairy called

24:21.120 --> 24:22.380
the Blue Fairy.

24:23.360 --> 24:24.960
She always helps Pinocchio.

24:26.200 --> 24:30.200
In Cinderella, a fairy godmother is Cinderella's good

24:30.200 --> 24:30.640
friend.

24:31.640 --> 24:34.640
There are fairies in one of William Shakespeare's

24:34.640 --> 24:35.520
plays too.

24:36.440 --> 24:40.500
In A Midsummer Night's Dream, Oberon and Titania

24:40.500 --> 24:43.320
are the king and queen of the fairies.

24:43.820 --> 24:46.560
They live in the forest and are important

24:46.560 --> 24:47.940
characters in the play.

24:49.520 --> 24:52.320
What some people say about fairies.

24:53.040 --> 24:55.280
They are small and have wings.

24:55.280 --> 24:59.180
They live in the forest, in trees, in

24:59.180 --> 25:00.900
flowers and in gardens.

25:02.000 --> 25:05.600
They are sometimes good and sometimes bad.

25:06.520 --> 25:07.220
They are magic.

25:08.120 --> 25:10.860
They can do good things and bad things.

25:14.200 --> 25:17.420
Chapter 4 Danger in the Lagoon

25:18.620 --> 25:22.700
Peter, Wendy, John, Michael and the Lost Boys

25:22.700 --> 25:25.440
often go to the Mermaid's Lagoon.

25:26.420 --> 25:28.460
The water is blue and beautiful.

25:29.520 --> 25:32.020
They like swimming and playing in the Blue

25:32.020 --> 25:32.520
Lagoon.

25:33.740 --> 25:37.900
Beautiful mermaids live here and they are Peter's

25:37.900 --> 25:38.140
friends.

25:38.960 --> 25:41.980
They have got long hair and are very

25:41.980 --> 25:42.400
pretty.

25:43.340 --> 25:47.300
They play mermaid games and then sit on

25:47.300 --> 25:50.640
marooners' rock and comb their long hair.

25:51.580 --> 25:54.580
They sit in the sun and talk and

25:54.580 --> 25:54.880
laugh.

25:55.800 --> 25:58.820
The children like the mermaids and John says,

25:59.460 --> 26:02.120
I want to catch a mermaid.

26:02.620 --> 26:05.800
He tries, but the mermaid jumps into the

26:05.800 --> 26:07.540
water and swims away.

26:08.260 --> 26:09.320
Everyone laughs.

26:14.740 --> 26:18.480
It's very difficult to catch a mermaid.

26:18.740 --> 26:19.420
Says Peter.

26:20.200 --> 26:23.280
Suddenly Peter hears a noise and says,

26:24.020 --> 26:25.360
The pirates are coming.

26:26.040 --> 26:27.000
I can hear them.

26:27.700 --> 26:31.120
John, Michael and the Lost Boys jump into

26:31.120 --> 26:32.820
the water and swim away.

26:33.540 --> 26:35.160
They are afraid of the pirates.

26:36.180 --> 26:37.600
But Wendy stays with Peter.

26:37.600 --> 26:40.780
They hide behind marooners' rock.

26:42.140 --> 26:45.820
A small boat with two pirates is coming

26:45.820 --> 26:46.540
to the lagoon.

26:47.420 --> 26:49.360
One pirate is Smee.

26:49.820 --> 26:52.260
He is old and wears glasses.

26:53.740 --> 26:55.740
The other pirate is Starkey.

26:56.520 --> 26:58.580
He is young and has got a long

26:58.580 --> 26:59.080
nose.

27:00.300 --> 27:02.820
Tiger Lily is on the boat and she

27:02.820 --> 27:04.800
is a prisoner of the pirates.

27:06.260 --> 27:08.460
Let's leave her on this rock.

27:09.340 --> 27:10.400
Says Smee.

27:10.780 --> 27:14.520
When the sea rises, she's going to die.

27:16.120 --> 27:18.340
The two pirates laugh loudly.

27:19.400 --> 27:22.140
It is almost night and it is dark.

27:28.600 --> 27:30.040
Poor Tiger Lily.

27:30.040 --> 27:31.440
Thanks Peter.

27:31.960 --> 27:34.160
She is our good friend.

27:34.900 --> 27:36.340
I must save her.

27:37.040 --> 27:38.700
But what can I do?

27:39.640 --> 27:42.580
He thinks for a minute and then imitates

27:42.580 --> 27:44.240
Captain Hook's voice.

27:45.540 --> 27:49.420
Cut the ropes and let Tiger Lily go.

27:50.360 --> 27:52.120
Do as I say Smee.

27:53.000 --> 27:54.180
Let her go.

27:55.180 --> 27:59.420
The two pirates hear Captain Hook's voice and

27:59.420 --> 28:00.380
are very surprised.

28:01.620 --> 28:04.360
They look at each other and then they

28:04.360 --> 28:04.880
look around.

28:05.840 --> 28:08.520
Starkey says Smee.

28:08.740 --> 28:11.620
Can you hear Hook's voice?

28:12.400 --> 28:13.140
Yes.

28:13.840 --> 28:15.760
Says Starkey looking around.

28:16.440 --> 28:18.700
But I don't see Hook.

28:19.420 --> 28:22.860
We must listen to Hook and cut the

28:22.860 --> 28:23.140
ropes.

28:23.140 --> 28:25.080
Oops says Smee.

28:25.400 --> 28:26.620
Are you sure?

28:27.540 --> 28:28.640
Ask Starkey.

28:29.200 --> 28:30.700
Of course I'm sure.

28:31.320 --> 28:32.660
Says Smee.

28:33.320 --> 28:36.420
Starkey gets a knife and cuts the rope.

28:37.240 --> 28:38.520
Tiger Lily is free.

28:39.500 --> 28:42.200
She jumps into the water and swims away.

28:43.840 --> 28:47.560
Captain Hook is on his ship, the Jolly

28:47.560 --> 28:50.260
Roger, and he sees everything.

28:50.920 --> 28:54.800
He is very angry because Tiger Lily is

28:54.800 --> 28:55.060
free.

28:56.360 --> 28:59.840
Peter Pan is very clever.

29:00.940 --> 29:02.020
thinks Captain Hook.

29:03.180 --> 29:05.260
I must fight him.

29:06.520 --> 29:10.700
Captain Hook jumps into the water and swims

29:10.700 --> 29:11.120
to the rock.

29:12.100 --> 29:13.000
He fights with Peter.

29:14.160 --> 29:15.260
It is a long fight.

29:16.240 --> 29:19.240
Captain Hook hurts Peter with his big hook.

29:19.240 --> 29:22.200
But Peter does not stop fighting.

29:23.200 --> 29:23.800
He is brave.

29:25.120 --> 29:27.140
At last Peter wins the fight.

29:28.060 --> 29:31.420
Captain Hook is angry and swims back to

29:31.420 --> 29:32.100
the Jolly Roger.

29:33.180 --> 29:36.840
Peter and Wendy are now alone on the

29:36.840 --> 29:37.040
rock.

29:37.860 --> 29:40.700
What a terrible fight Peter.

29:41.200 --> 29:43.240
Says Wendy looking at Peter's hand.

29:43.900 --> 29:46.540
His hand is badly hurt after the fight

29:46.540 --> 29:47.460
with Captain Hook.

29:47.460 --> 29:49.860
Yes, says Peter.

29:50.540 --> 29:53.580
But I'm not afraid of Hook or the

29:53.580 --> 29:53.820
pirates.

29:54.880 --> 29:56.940
You're a very brave boy.

29:57.500 --> 29:58.800
Says Wendy, smiling.

29:59.560 --> 30:01.400
Look, says Peter.

30:01.960 --> 30:04.480
The sea is rising and we are in

30:04.480 --> 30:05.960
great danger here.

30:06.580 --> 30:07.780
What can we do?

30:08.700 --> 30:09.400
asks Wendy.

30:10.040 --> 30:12.880
We must leave this rock immediately.

30:13.660 --> 30:15.660
Says Peter, looking at the sea.

30:15.660 --> 30:17.060
Oh Peter.

30:17.920 --> 30:18.540
Says Wendy.

30:19.280 --> 30:22.860
I can't swim or fly because I'm very

30:22.860 --> 30:23.620
tired.

30:24.260 --> 30:25.680
Peter thinks for a moment.

30:26.280 --> 30:28.440
He sees a big kite with a long

30:28.440 --> 30:28.900
tail.

30:29.660 --> 30:32.280
It is flying slowly over the lagoon.

30:32.980 --> 30:35.140
He quickly takes the tail of the kite

30:35.140 --> 30:35.960
and says,

30:36.920 --> 30:40.060
Wendy, hold on to this tail and fly

30:40.060 --> 30:41.640
away with the kite.

30:42.640 --> 30:45.540
Wendy flies away with the kite.

30:46.480 --> 30:48.580
The sea is rising quickly.

30:49.260 --> 30:49.800
Peter thinks.

30:50.480 --> 30:52.000
I must fly away.

30:53.080 --> 30:57.100
When Peter gets home, everyone is happy to

30:57.100 --> 30:57.680
see him.

31:01.120 --> 31:03.780
Chapter 5. A Secret Place

31:05.800 --> 31:09.680
The underground home is a secret place in

31:09.680 --> 31:10.440
the big forest.

31:10.440 --> 31:14.440
It is a safe place because no one

31:14.440 --> 31:15.560
knows where it is.

31:16.540 --> 31:18.940
There is only one big room with a

31:18.940 --> 31:19.260
fireplace.

31:20.640 --> 31:23.180
It is a happy, warm home.

31:24.540 --> 31:27.120
Wendy, John and Michael are very happy there.

31:28.220 --> 31:30.260
Wendy is a wonderful mother.

31:31.240 --> 31:33.560
She cooks and so's for everyone.

31:34.680 --> 31:38.660
Every evening, after dinner, everyone sits in front

31:38.660 --> 31:39.360
of the fireplace.

31:40.040 --> 31:42.820
Wendy tells great bedtime stories.

31:44.200 --> 31:46.760
The lost boys love these stories and are

31:46.760 --> 31:50.000
happy because they finally have a mother.

31:51.360 --> 31:54.160
John and Michael are happy because there is

31:54.160 --> 31:55.980
an exciting adventure every day.

31:57.160 --> 31:58.280
They are never bored.

31:59.860 --> 32:01.680
Peter Pan is the perfect father.

32:02.580 --> 32:05.940
He brings home food and protects his family.

32:06.940 --> 32:09.300
He and Wendy play games with the children

32:09.300 --> 32:10.900
and laugh with them.

32:11.780 --> 32:14.540
Everyone is having a wonderful time.

32:16.040 --> 32:20.640
But in London, Mr. and Mrs. Darling are

32:20.640 --> 32:21.280
not happy.

32:22.140 --> 32:25.920
They are very sad because they can't find

32:25.920 --> 32:26.980
their three children.

32:28.300 --> 32:29.920
And Nana is sad too.

32:31.420 --> 32:33.920
Where are our three children?

32:34.800 --> 32:36.000
They think.

32:37.320 --> 32:40.260
Wendy sometimes thinks about her parents.

32:41.360 --> 32:44.360
One evening, she says...

32:44.360 --> 32:47.620
This evening, I'm going to tell you a

32:47.620 --> 32:49.500
new bedtime story.

32:50.360 --> 32:52.120
It takes place in England.

32:53.760 --> 32:56.620
Everyone sits down in front of the fireplace

32:56.620 --> 32:58.420
and listens to her.

32:59.420 --> 33:02.640
In the city of London, there are two

33:02.640 --> 33:03.340
parents.

33:04.340 --> 33:08.100
They're very sad because they can't find their

33:08.100 --> 33:09.100
three children.

33:09.960 --> 33:14.500
Every night, they leave the nursery window open.

33:15.460 --> 33:17.520
They want their children to return.

33:18.680 --> 33:22.840
They wait and wait, but their three children

33:22.840 --> 33:23.840
don't return.

33:24.840 --> 33:28.900
These poor parents are terribly sad.

33:29.960 --> 33:32.200
But Wendy...

33:32.200 --> 33:33.540
Say John and Michael.

33:34.160 --> 33:37.040
That's the story of our parents.

33:38.260 --> 33:42.180
Peter listens to the story and says...

33:42.180 --> 33:47.000
Sometimes parents forget their children and other children

33:47.000 --> 33:48.180
take their place.

33:49.300 --> 33:52.380
Wendy, John and Michael are surprised.

33:53.840 --> 33:54.580
They look at Peter.

33:55.520 --> 33:57.180
Are you sure, Peter?

33:57.640 --> 33:58.320
asks Wendy.

33:59.080 --> 34:01.720
Yes, I'm sure, says Peter.

34:02.440 --> 34:05.780
Perhaps there are other children in our nursery

34:05.780 --> 34:07.520
and in our beds.

34:08.340 --> 34:08.680
Says Wendy.

34:10.540 --> 34:14.500
John, Michael, we must go home immediately.

34:15.620 --> 34:19.700
John and Michael look at Wendy and say...

34:19.700 --> 34:21.760
Do we really have to go?

34:21.760 --> 34:25.120
Yes, we must go home.

34:25.400 --> 34:25.960
Says Wendy.

34:26.680 --> 34:29.540
Quickly, we haven't got much time.

34:30.280 --> 34:33.200
But we're happy here in Neverland with Peter

34:33.200 --> 34:34.560
and the Lost Boys.

34:35.100 --> 34:35.720
Says John.

34:36.380 --> 34:38.960
There's a new adventure every day.

34:39.740 --> 34:40.400
Says Michael.

34:40.960 --> 34:42.680
And we're never bored.

34:43.160 --> 34:43.780
Says John.

34:44.740 --> 34:46.840
Neverland is a wonderful place.

34:47.760 --> 34:49.160
Oh, Wendy.

34:50.440 --> 34:51.640
Say the Lost Boys.

34:53.140 --> 34:55.400
Please don't go away.

34:56.420 --> 34:57.900
Don't leave us.

34:58.860 --> 35:03.260
Wendy looks at the Lost Boys and says...

35:03.260 --> 35:04.640
Please don't be sad.

35:05.500 --> 35:07.860
You can come to London and live with

35:07.860 --> 35:08.120
us.

35:08.780 --> 35:11.400
You can be part of the Darling family.

35:12.660 --> 35:14.160
Oh, Wendy.

35:14.160 --> 35:16.600
Say the Lost Boys.

35:17.560 --> 35:18.820
Thank you.

35:19.540 --> 35:20.520
That's wonderful.

35:22.340 --> 35:26.620
We can have a real family in London.

35:29.220 --> 35:32.440
Nibs and tutels jump up and down and

35:32.440 --> 35:32.880
laugh.

35:34.080 --> 35:36.400
The other Lost Boys dance around the room.

35:37.400 --> 35:38.620
They are very happy.

35:39.660 --> 35:41.940
Peter is not happy.

35:42.680 --> 35:45.180
I'm not coming with you to London.

35:45.920 --> 35:48.980
Everyone is surprised and looks at him.

35:49.660 --> 35:50.300
Why?

35:51.000 --> 35:51.800
asks Wendy.

35:52.680 --> 35:54.800
I don't want to grow up.

35:55.420 --> 35:56.060
Says Peter.

35:56.980 --> 35:59.600
I don't want to become an adult.

36:00.740 --> 36:02.400
I want to be a boy forever.

36:03.440 --> 36:04.400
But Peter.

36:05.420 --> 36:05.740
Says Wendy.

36:06.700 --> 36:09.120
All boys and girls grow up.

36:09.120 --> 36:11.460
They become adults.

36:12.180 --> 36:12.640
No.

36:13.400 --> 36:15.120
Says Peter angrily.

36:15.980 --> 36:18.040
I don't want to grow up.

36:18.700 --> 36:21.480
You can go, but I'm not coming.

36:22.620 --> 36:25.300
He turns around and looks at the wall.

36:26.900 --> 36:31.160
Wendy, John, Michael and the Lost Boys say

36:31.160 --> 36:32.260
goodbye to Peter

36:32.260 --> 36:34.820
and leave the underground home.

36:36.200 --> 36:38.820
They start to walk in the forest.

36:40.220 --> 36:42.660
But they don't know that the pirates are

36:42.660 --> 36:43.920
hiding behind the trees.

36:44.980 --> 36:46.360
They are waiting for them.

36:47.300 --> 36:50.060
Suddenly the pirates jump out of the forest.

36:51.180 --> 36:54.200
The children are very surprised and try to

36:54.200 --> 36:54.640
run away.

36:55.660 --> 36:57.520
But there are a lot of pirates.

36:58.840 --> 37:00.500
And they take the children to the Jolly

37:00.500 --> 37:00.860
Roger.

37:02.760 --> 37:06.420
Peter is inside the underground home and he

37:06.420 --> 37:07.580
does not hear anything.

37:08.960 --> 37:11.720
He sits in front of the fireplace and

37:11.720 --> 37:15.280
thinks about Wendy, John and Michael and the

37:15.280 --> 37:15.760
Lost Boys.

37:17.080 --> 37:18.600
He is sad without them.

37:20.020 --> 37:20.580
Tap.

37:21.280 --> 37:21.560
Tap.

37:21.840 --> 37:21.940
Tap.

37:23.220 --> 37:24.680
There is someone at the door.

37:25.820 --> 37:27.360
Peter goes to the door and asks,

37:27.360 --> 37:29.000
Who's there?

37:29.920 --> 37:31.480
He hears the sound of little bells.

37:33.820 --> 37:35.800
And opens the door.

37:36.760 --> 37:38.340
Tinkerbell flies in and says,

37:39.240 --> 37:41.000
The children are with the pirates.

37:42.280 --> 37:45.140
What do you mean, Tink? asks Peter.

37:46.120 --> 37:50.500
Wendy, John, Michael and the Lost Boys are

37:50.500 --> 37:53.140
on the Jolly Roger with Captain Hook.

37:53.700 --> 37:54.680
Says Tinkerbell.

37:54.680 --> 37:56.160
They're in danger.

37:57.020 --> 37:57.780
Oh no.

37:58.460 --> 37:59.100
Says Peter.

37:59.680 --> 38:01.260
We must save them.

38:01.820 --> 38:04.220
Let's go to the Jolly Roger quickly.

38:05.040 --> 38:07.140
I want to fight Hook.

38:08.180 --> 38:12.160
Peter and Tinkerbell leave the underground home and

38:12.160 --> 38:13.680
fly to the Jolly Roger.

38:16.340 --> 38:19.240
The Great Ormond Street Hospital for Children.

38:20.080 --> 38:22.760
In London, there is a hospital for sick

38:22.760 --> 38:25.920
children called the Great Ormond Street Hospital for

38:25.920 --> 38:26.160
Children.

38:27.260 --> 38:30.280
J.M. Barry likes children very much.

38:31.120 --> 38:33.260
He wants children to be well and happy.

38:34.160 --> 38:36.900
He often visits this hospital because he wants

38:36.900 --> 38:37.860
to help the children.

38:39.020 --> 38:40.580
Barry is a kind man.

38:40.580 --> 38:44.760
In 1929, he decides that all the money

38:44.760 --> 38:48.380
from book sales, films and theatre plays of

38:48.380 --> 38:50.620
Peter Pan goes to the hospital.

38:51.700 --> 38:52.940
And this continues today.

38:54.000 --> 38:57.420
This money helps the hospital, the children, the

38:57.420 --> 38:58.940
doctors and the nurses.

39:00.300 --> 39:02.440
The children at the hospital can watch the

39:02.440 --> 39:04.580
play Peter Pan once a year.

39:05.310 --> 39:08.680
This is a very happy moment for them.

39:11.240 --> 39:12.660
Chapter 6

39:13.580 --> 39:14.740
The Pirate Ship

39:15.660 --> 39:19.260
The Jolly Roger is a big pirate ship

39:19.260 --> 39:21.580
in the bay near Kid's Creek.

39:22.380 --> 39:25.180
On the ship, there is a black flag

39:25.180 --> 39:27.380
with a white skull on it.

39:28.260 --> 39:29.860
It is the pirate's flag.

39:30.560 --> 39:32.500
It is night time.

39:33.480 --> 39:35.700
And there is a yellow moon in the

39:35.700 --> 39:36.360
dark sky.

39:38.160 --> 39:40.680
Peter sees the children on the pirate ship.

39:41.880 --> 39:43.520
They are prisoners of Captain Hook.

39:44.620 --> 39:45.840
And they are afraid of him.

39:47.080 --> 39:50.380
Captain Hook looks at the children and says,

39:51.520 --> 39:54.560
Peter Pan can't save you now.

39:55.680 --> 39:57.080
You're my prisoners.

39:57.080 --> 39:59.960
He starts to laugh.

40:00.920 --> 40:02.780
And the other pirates laugh too.

40:03.500 --> 40:04.140
Ha ha!

40:04.680 --> 40:06.680
Smee, come here.

40:07.580 --> 40:08.720
Says Captain Hook.

40:09.440 --> 40:10.680
Yes, sir.

40:11.380 --> 40:12.460
Says Smee.

40:13.020 --> 40:16.560
Get the plank ready for these children.

40:17.600 --> 40:18.880
Says Captain Hook.

40:19.620 --> 40:20.700
You're all right, sir.

40:21.480 --> 40:22.420
Says Smee.

40:22.840 --> 40:25.240
He goes to get the long plank.

40:26.240 --> 40:27.460
What's the plank?

40:28.220 --> 40:30.380
Asks John looking at Wendy.

40:31.760 --> 40:32.460
Ha ha!

40:33.280 --> 40:34.380
Laughs Captain Hook.

40:35.160 --> 40:38.460
You don't know what the plank is.

40:39.080 --> 40:43.260
You must all walk the plank tonight.

40:44.280 --> 40:45.800
I don't understand.

40:47.200 --> 40:48.020
Says John.

40:48.880 --> 40:50.800
First you walk the plank.

40:51.430 --> 40:54.620
And then you fall into the sea.

40:55.900 --> 40:57.000
Says Captain Hook.

40:57.620 --> 41:01.780
And in the sea there's a hungry crocodile.

41:02.360 --> 41:04.160
He wants to eat too.

41:04.880 --> 41:05.460
Ha ha!

41:07.040 --> 41:08.320
Oh no!

41:09.200 --> 41:10.240
Shout the children.

41:10.920 --> 41:12.180
They are afraid.

41:13.220 --> 41:17.720
But perhaps I can save two of you.

41:18.530 --> 41:19.640
Says Captain Hook.

41:20.100 --> 41:21.080
Looking at the children.

41:22.060 --> 41:24.360
I want two young pirates.

41:25.500 --> 41:27.740
Who wants to be a pirate?

41:29.280 --> 41:31.240
The lost boys look at John.

41:32.320 --> 41:35.400
And John looks at Michael and says...

41:35.400 --> 41:37.680
I don't want to walk the plank.

41:38.520 --> 41:40.520
I don't want to be food for that

41:40.520 --> 41:42.000
hungry crocodile.

41:42.740 --> 41:44.640
What do you mean, John?

41:44.640 --> 41:46.040
Asks Michael.

41:46.800 --> 41:47.380
Well.

41:47.880 --> 41:48.520
Says John.

41:49.240 --> 41:51.340
The life of a pirate is exciting.

41:52.420 --> 41:53.720
There are a lot of adventures.

41:54.540 --> 41:56.560
Let's be pirates, Michael.

41:57.220 --> 41:59.540
Michael does not know what to say.

42:00.400 --> 42:01.840
He and John look at Wendy.

42:02.880 --> 42:05.580
That's a terrible idea, John.

42:06.020 --> 42:06.640
Says Wendy.

42:07.420 --> 42:09.340
I'm surprised at you.

42:09.960 --> 42:13.200
Captain Hook moves his hook in front of

42:13.200 --> 42:13.740
their faces

42:13.740 --> 42:15.460
and laughs loudly.

42:16.480 --> 42:17.380
Ha ha!

42:17.820 --> 42:20.120
I want an answer from you.

42:21.080 --> 42:22.320
Says Captain Hook.

42:22.960 --> 42:25.320
Do you want to be pirates?

42:26.260 --> 42:28.420
Yes or no.

42:30.610 --> 42:33.540
John and Michael look at each other and

42:33.540 --> 42:34.740
then say...

42:35.400 --> 42:35.980
Never!

42:36.940 --> 42:37.520
What?

42:38.580 --> 42:40.680
Says Captain Hook angrily.

42:41.420 --> 42:45.900
Then you must walk the plank and die.

42:47.480 --> 42:48.860
Wendy is afraid.

42:49.780 --> 42:52.320
She loves her brothers and the lost boys.

42:53.340 --> 42:54.800
She has tears in her eyes.

42:55.880 --> 42:57.800
A pirate shouts...

42:57.800 --> 43:00.500
Who's the first to walk the plank?

43:01.540 --> 43:05.360
At that moment, everyone hears a loud noise.

43:06.280 --> 43:09.120
Tick, tock, tick, tock.

43:09.940 --> 43:10.580
Oh no.

43:11.760 --> 43:13.120
It's the crocodile.

43:13.720 --> 43:14.820
Says Captain Hook.

43:15.380 --> 43:17.540
He wants to eat me.

43:18.780 --> 43:22.480
His face is white and he runs to

43:22.480 --> 43:24.580
his cabin and hides there.

43:25.260 --> 43:28.440
The crocodile is hungry tonight.

43:29.900 --> 43:30.780
Says a pirate.

43:31.900 --> 43:34.580
Someone must walk the plank.

43:35.800 --> 43:38.340
Who's the first to walk the plank?

43:39.260 --> 43:42.160
asks me, looking at John and Michael.

43:43.060 --> 43:44.100
Let's go!

43:45.340 --> 43:50.420
Suddenly, Peter Pan arrives and Tinkerbell follows him.

43:51.380 --> 43:54.640
Wendy, John, Michael and the lost boys cheer

43:54.640 --> 43:55.260
happily.

43:56.260 --> 43:58.080
They are very happy to see him.

43:59.620 --> 44:00.660
Peter's here!

44:01.660 --> 44:02.620
They say.

44:03.320 --> 44:05.500
He's going to save us!

44:06.680 --> 44:10.260
Captain Hook comes out of his cabin and

44:10.260 --> 44:11.420
sees Peter Pan.

44:12.360 --> 44:15.480
He and his pirates are very angry.

44:16.320 --> 44:19.240
Hook takes his long sword and says,

44:20.520 --> 44:23.660
I'm going to fight you, Peter Pan.

44:24.420 --> 44:29.580
This is your last fight because tonight you're

44:29.580 --> 44:30.640
going to die.

44:30.640 --> 44:30.820
Die!

44:32.720 --> 44:36.460
Hook fights with his long sword and with

44:36.460 --> 44:37.360
his big hook.

44:38.260 --> 44:41.120
Peter is very brave and fights with his

44:41.120 --> 44:42.360
small sword.

44:43.520 --> 44:45.340
He pushes Hook to the back of the

44:45.340 --> 44:45.560
ship.

44:46.680 --> 44:47.780
It is a terrible fight.

44:48.960 --> 44:52.220
John, Michael and the lost boys fight the

44:52.220 --> 44:52.520
pirates.

44:53.560 --> 44:57.080
After a long fight, they throw the pirates

44:57.080 --> 44:58.460
into the sea.

44:59.880 --> 45:03.720
Peter and Captain Hook fight all over the

45:03.720 --> 45:03.980
ship.

45:05.140 --> 45:06.800
Their swords make a lot of noise.

45:07.740 --> 45:11.080
Suddenly, Peter pushes Captain Hook into the sea.

45:11.940 --> 45:12.800
Hook shouts,

45:13.900 --> 45:15.140
Oh no!

45:16.700 --> 45:19.840
He falls into the sea and into the

45:19.840 --> 45:22.500
mouth of the hungry crocodile.

45:23.080 --> 45:24.420
Everyone cheers!

45:25.720 --> 45:27.300
Oh Peter!

45:28.000 --> 45:29.260
Says Wendy happily.

45:29.920 --> 45:32.120
You're a very brave boy.

45:33.040 --> 45:36.200
She smiles and kisses him on the cheek.

45:37.500 --> 45:39.300
Peter is happy and says,

45:40.040 --> 45:42.740
Now the Jolly Roger is ours!

45:43.800 --> 45:44.780
We can go home!

45:46.380 --> 45:46.980
Home!

45:48.000 --> 45:49.060
Everyone shouts.

45:50.220 --> 45:51.280
Let's go!

45:55.160 --> 45:56.040
Chapter 7

45:56.040 --> 45:57.980
Back in London

45:59.260 --> 46:02.700
The Darling home in London is a very

46:02.700 --> 46:04.080
sad place.

46:04.640 --> 46:08.360
Mr. and Mrs. Darling never smile or laugh.

46:09.260 --> 46:13.300
They always think about Wendy, John and Michael.

46:14.540 --> 46:15.960
Every morning at breakfast,

46:16.940 --> 46:19.520
Mrs. Darling looks at the three empty chairs

46:19.520 --> 46:20.080
and says,

46:20.080 --> 46:23.260
Where are my children?

46:24.760 --> 46:26.300
She has tears in her eyes.

46:27.760 --> 46:31.000
Nanna goes to the nursery and sees three

46:31.000 --> 46:31.880
empty beds.

46:32.900 --> 46:36.500
In the evening, Mr. Darling comes home after

46:36.500 --> 46:36.840
work

46:36.840 --> 46:39.880
and he does not hear his children talking

46:39.880 --> 46:40.600
and laughing.

46:42.280 --> 46:45.640
Mrs. Darling often sits in the silent nursery

46:45.640 --> 46:47.120
and cries.

46:47.120 --> 46:52.560
She thinks of her children, their games and

46:52.560 --> 46:53.400
their happy voices.

46:54.720 --> 46:56.380
Nanna tries to comfort her,

46:57.260 --> 47:00.020
but nothing can make Mrs. Darling happy.

47:01.240 --> 47:04.320
She always leaves the nursery window open.

47:06.020 --> 47:09.700
Then one night, something wonderful happens.

47:10.880 --> 47:16.140
Wendy, John and Michael fly into the nursery

47:16.980 --> 47:20.300
Mrs. Darling is sitting near the fireplace and

47:20.300 --> 47:21.460
thinking about her children.

47:22.220 --> 47:24.320
She hears a voice and turns around.

47:24.920 --> 47:26.480
Mother! Mother!

47:26.940 --> 47:28.100
cries Wendy happily.

47:28.680 --> 47:29.240
We home!

47:30.280 --> 47:33.220
Mrs. Darling sees Wendy, John and Michael.

47:34.240 --> 47:35.260
She is very surprised.

47:36.400 --> 47:37.840
She cannot believe her eyes.

47:38.800 --> 47:39.480
Oh!

47:40.820 --> 47:41.820
She cries.

47:42.920 --> 47:47.200
Is this true or is it a dream?

47:48.680 --> 47:49.660
Mother!

47:50.520 --> 47:52.120
The children say.

47:53.500 --> 47:54.500
It's true!

47:55.760 --> 47:56.920
We're home!

47:57.960 --> 48:00.980
They hug their mother and kiss her.

48:01.760 --> 48:04.860
It's wonderful to see you!

48:05.440 --> 48:08.900
Says Mrs. Darling, looking at her three children.

48:08.900 --> 48:11.800
Oh, let me look at you.

48:12.640 --> 48:15.880
How wonderful to hear your sweet voices.

48:16.820 --> 48:20.240
Nanna runs into the nursery and barks happily.

48:24.900 --> 48:28.420
The children are very pleased to see her.

48:29.160 --> 48:31.340
I must call your father.

48:31.900 --> 48:32.800
Says Mrs. Darling.

48:34.040 --> 48:38.240
George, George, come to the nursery immediately.

48:38.900 --> 48:42.580
Mr. Darling comes to the nursery and sees

48:42.580 --> 48:43.760
his three children.

48:44.220 --> 48:48.560
Oh, this is a wonderful night.

48:49.240 --> 48:50.160
He says happily.

48:50.960 --> 48:53.820
Our children are finally home.

48:54.900 --> 48:55.740
Mother!

48:56.280 --> 48:56.820
Says Wendy.

48:58.260 --> 49:00.620
Peter Pan and the lost boys are here

49:00.620 --> 49:01.000
too.

49:01.820 --> 49:03.000
They're waiting outside.

49:04.720 --> 49:06.680
Ask them to come inside.

49:06.680 --> 49:08.700
Says Mrs. Darling.

49:09.660 --> 49:13.500
The six lost boys slowly enter the nursery

49:13.500 --> 49:17.100
and look at Mr. and Mrs. Darling and

49:17.100 --> 49:17.460
Nanna.

49:18.420 --> 49:19.140
Mother?

49:19.720 --> 49:20.360
Says Wendy.

49:21.240 --> 49:23.060
These are the lost boys.

49:23.980 --> 49:26.960
They haven't got a family or a mother.

49:27.920 --> 49:29.360
Can they stay with us?

49:30.000 --> 49:35.980
Oh, these dear little boys haven't got a

49:35.980 --> 49:37.960
family or a mother.

49:38.540 --> 49:39.580
Says Mrs. Darling.

49:40.160 --> 49:43.180
Of course they can stay with us.

49:43.960 --> 49:46.100
We're their new family.

49:47.140 --> 49:49.260
Thank you Mrs. Darling.

49:50.580 --> 49:52.080
Say the lost boys.

49:53.180 --> 49:55.580
But where is Peter Pan?

49:56.320 --> 49:59.700
asks Mrs. Darling, looking around the nursery.

50:01.040 --> 50:03.760
Peter Pan comes into the nursery and says,

50:04.320 --> 50:07.620
Here I am, but I don't want to

50:07.620 --> 50:08.420
stay here.

50:09.240 --> 50:12.860
Everyone is surprised, and Mrs. Darling asks,

50:13.520 --> 50:16.300
Why don't you want to stay here?

50:17.040 --> 50:19.560
I don't want to go to school and

50:19.560 --> 50:20.580
learn things.

50:21.220 --> 50:21.860
Says Peter.

50:22.440 --> 50:24.200
I don't want to grow up.

50:24.200 --> 50:27.360
I want to be a young boy and

50:27.360 --> 50:28.980
have lots of fun forever.

50:30.080 --> 50:31.100
But Peter.

50:32.080 --> 50:33.360
Says Wendy sadly.

50:34.240 --> 50:36.260
I must go back to Neverland.

50:36.720 --> 50:37.420
Says Peter.

50:38.160 --> 50:41.100
My home and my friends are there.

50:41.960 --> 50:45.460
I'm happy with the Indians and the fairies.

50:46.340 --> 50:49.320
Wendy is surprised and asks,

50:49.920 --> 50:52.260
When can I see you then?

50:53.200 --> 50:56.300
Mrs. Darling thinks for a moment and says,

50:57.600 --> 50:59.480
I have a good idea.

51:00.140 --> 51:04.280
Wendy, you can visit Peter in Neverland every

51:04.280 --> 51:05.020
spring.

51:05.800 --> 51:08.060
You can stay there for a week.

51:09.920 --> 51:13.040
Can I really go to Neverland every spring

51:13.040 --> 51:13.520
mother?

51:14.200 --> 51:14.720
asks Wendy.

51:15.660 --> 51:17.260
Of course you can.

51:18.300 --> 51:20.640
Says Mrs. Darling, smiling.

51:21.460 --> 51:24.680
Peter looks at Mrs. Darling and asks,

51:25.160 --> 51:26.180
Is that a promise?

51:27.000 --> 51:28.500
Of course it is.

51:28.900 --> 51:30.020
Says Mrs. Darling.

51:30.780 --> 51:33.320
Then I want spring to come quickly.

51:33.920 --> 51:35.220
Says Peter happily.

51:36.480 --> 51:37.280
Yes.

51:37.960 --> 51:38.740
Very quickly.

51:39.600 --> 51:40.940
Says Wendy laughing.

51:41.860 --> 51:43.220
Come on Tink.

51:43.700 --> 51:44.280
Says Peter.

51:44.800 --> 51:47.900
Let's fly home and wait for spring.

51:49.000 --> 51:52.780
Peter Pan and Tinkerbell fly out of the

51:52.780 --> 51:53.540
nursery window

51:53.540 --> 51:55.500
and into the night sky.

51:56.800 --> 51:59.340
They are flying to Neverland.

52:02.620 --> 52:03.840
Exercise three.

52:04.940 --> 52:07.400
Wendy is taking the Lost Boys on a

52:07.400 --> 52:08.540
short tour of London.

52:09.560 --> 52:11.680
She is giving them some information about the

52:11.680 --> 52:11.960
city.

52:13.060 --> 52:15.660
Listen to her and then choose the correct

52:15.660 --> 52:16.180
answer.

52:18.040 --> 52:21.100
Today we are going to visit some interesting

52:21.100 --> 52:22.920
places in London.

52:23.980 --> 52:26.180
The first place we are going to see

52:26.180 --> 52:27.420
is Big Ben,

52:28.140 --> 52:31.000
the big clock tower near the houses of

52:31.000 --> 52:31.240
Parliament.

52:32.480 --> 52:34.940
Look at the clock at the top of

52:34.940 --> 52:35.420
the tower.

52:36.720 --> 52:38.940
Now we are going to travel on the

52:38.940 --> 52:39.660
River Thames.

52:40.660 --> 52:41.940
Let's buy tickets.

52:41.940 --> 52:45.400
It's always fun to ride a boat on

52:45.400 --> 52:45.800
the river.

52:47.320 --> 52:49.360
We are going to see Tower Bridge.

52:50.520 --> 52:54.220
The bridge sometimes opens up to let big

52:54.220 --> 52:55.180
ships pass.

52:56.760 --> 53:00.200
The Tower of London is near Tower Bridge.

53:01.160 --> 53:03.840
It's very old and a lot of people

53:03.840 --> 53:04.560
visit it.

53:05.900 --> 53:08.840
Let's walk by this beautiful church.

53:08.840 --> 53:11.000
It's St Paul's Cathedral.

53:12.200 --> 53:14.680
The people of London love this church.

53:15.760 --> 53:19.200
Oh, it's a quarter past one and time

53:19.200 --> 53:19.740
for lunch.

53:20.620 --> 53:23.580
After lunch we are going to Hyde Park.

53:24.520 --> 53:26.460
It's a wonderful big park.

53:27.400 --> 53:30.320
We can play there until half past four.

53:31.220 --> 53:32.960
Then we must go home for tea.

53:36.100 --> 53:37.440
The Darling Home.

53:38.440 --> 53:41.320
What does the Darling Home in London look

53:41.320 --> 53:41.620
like?

53:42.340 --> 53:45.020
It is a comfortable home with a nice

53:45.020 --> 53:45.400
garden.

53:46.480 --> 53:48.920
On the ground floor there is a dining

53:48.920 --> 53:49.300
room.

53:50.280 --> 53:51.960
The family has its meals here.

53:53.100 --> 53:55.260
There is a long table with a lot

53:55.260 --> 53:56.380
of chairs around it.

53:57.300 --> 53:59.500
There are also pictures on the walls.

53:59.500 --> 54:03.360
On the ground floor there is also a

54:03.360 --> 54:04.400
large sitting room

54:04.400 --> 54:07.760
with a big sofa and comfortable chairs.

54:08.720 --> 54:11.440
People sit here in the evening and read

54:11.440 --> 54:12.500
or talk.

54:13.720 --> 54:15.320
They also listen to music.

54:16.780 --> 54:18.860
Families like singing together.

54:19.740 --> 54:21.440
Often someone plays the piano.

54:22.520 --> 54:25.120
When friends come to visit they sit in

54:25.120 --> 54:25.740
the sitting room.

54:26.600 --> 54:29.300
At the back of the house there is

54:29.300 --> 54:30.060
a big kitchen.

54:31.300 --> 54:33.680
Next to the kitchen there is a small

54:33.680 --> 54:36.000
room called the Scullery.

54:37.000 --> 54:39.080
This is where the servants wash up.

54:40.740 --> 54:44.800
Some big houses have breakfast rooms and libraries.

54:46.220 --> 54:48.620
On the first floor there are the bedrooms,

54:49.460 --> 54:51.380
the bathroom and the nursery.

54:52.380 --> 54:54.920
The rooms have open fireplaces.

54:56.280 --> 54:59.260
The servants live in rooms at the top

54:59.260 --> 54:59.900
of the house.

